OL,6,FA hypnotist accused of murder would
OL,7,Fhave "shouting matches" with her
OL,8,Fhusband and they would swear at each
OL,9,Fother in front of their granddaughter,
OL,10,Fa court has heard.JChristine Rawle,
OL,11,F70, is .JMrs Rawle's granddaughter,
OL,12,FGeorgina Bufton, was asked about her
OL,13,Fchildhood visits to their home near
OL,14,FBraunton.J"My grandad was a very
OL,15,Fdismissive man," she said.J"He would
OL,16,Fattack her femininity and try to
OL,17,Fdisempower her. Any woman would react
OL,18,Fto that.J"It would end with an 'F you'
OL,19,Fon that side, and an 'F you' on this
OL,20,Fside, and then it would dissipate
OL,21,Funtil the next day."JAsked whether she
OL,22,Fwitnessed any violence, Ms Bufton
OL,23,Fsaid: "I think I saw nan slap him
OL,24,Fduring an argument, but I think it was
OL,25,Fvery well deserved."
